===Etymology===
Coined possibly independently multiple times in multiple languages, but modern use derives from the {{etyl|ia|en}} word. The word itself comes from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|inter||between}} + {{m|la|lingua||language}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|ĭn'tə(r)lĭng"wə}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈɪntə(ɹ)ˌlɪŋɡwə/}}

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# An [[interlanguage]] based on Romance languages, English, German, Russian and Latin, developed by the [[International Auxiliary Language Association]], and first published in 1951.
# [[Latino sine flexione]], a simplified version of Latin by Giuseppe Peano

